    <h1>Main Characters of Middle-earth</h1>

<p>
    Explore the legendary heroes and  villains of J.R.R. Tolkien’s world.
    Each character below includes an image  and a short description.
</p>

<div>
        <h3>Frodo Baggins</h3>
        <p>A quiet hobbit from the Shire chosen to carry the One Ring to Mordor. Though not a warrior, his courage and endurance make him one of Middle-earth’s greatest heroes.</p>
        <p>&nbsp;<img src="///images/images/Frodo.jpg" />
        </p>
    </div>
    <div>
        <h3>Samwise Gamgee</h3>
        <p>Frodo’s loyal friend and gardener. Sam’s bravery, kindness, and determination often save the mission when hope seems lost. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<img src="///images/images/Sam.jpg" style="width: 298px" /></p>
    </div>

  <div>
        <h3>Gandalf</h3>
        <p>A wise and powerful wizard who guides the Fellowship. He inspires others to be brave and stands against the darkness spreading across Middle-earth.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;<img src="///images/images/Gandalf.jpg" style="width: 296px"/></p>
    </div>

    <div>
        <h3>Aragorn</h3>
        <p>A ranger of the North who is revealed to be the heir to Gondor’s throne. Strong, humble, and noble, he leads the forces of men in the final war against Sauron.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;<img src="///images/images/Aragorn.jpg" style="width: 292px; height: 396px" /></p>
    </div>

    <div>
        <h3>Legolas</h3>
        <p>An elven prince from Mirkwood, gifted with incredible eyesight, agility, and skill with a bow. Calm and graceful, he forms a strong friendship with Gimli.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;<img src="///images/images/Legolas.jpg" style="width: 359px" /></p>
    </div>
    <div>
        <h3>Gimli</h3>
        <p>A fierce dwarf warrior with a strong sense of honor. Although suspicious of elves at first, he becomes one of Legolas’s most loyal friends.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;<img src="///images/images/gimil.jpg" style="width: 366px; height: 486px" /></p>
    </div>

       <div>
        <h3>Boromir</h3>
        <p>Son of the Steward of Gondor, proud and brave. He is tempted by the Ring but ultimately redeems himself by protecting Merry and Pippin.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;<img src="///images/images/Boromir.jpg" style="width: 342px" /></p>
    </div>

     <div>
        <h3>Merry</h3>
        <p>A clever and adventurous hobbit. Merry helps rally the Riders of Rohan and plays a crucial role in defeating the Witch-King.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;<img src="///images/images/Merry.jpg" style="width: 342px" /></p>
    </div>
       <div>

        <h3>Pippin</h3>
        <p>Curious and sometimes reckless, but with a good heart. His journey teaches him responsibility and courage as he becomes a soldier of Gondor.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;<img src="///images/images/Pippin.jpg" style="width: 303px" /></p>
    </div>
       <div>
        <h3>Arwen</h3>
        <p>An elven princess who gives up immortality to be with Aragorn. Her grace and wisdom guide him toward his destiny.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;<img src="///images/images/Arwen.jpg" style="width: 289px" /></p>
    </div>
       <div>
 
        <h3>Éowyn</h3>
        <p>A noblewoman of Rohan who refuses to stay behind while others fight. She disguises herself as a warrior and defeats the Witch-King in battle.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;<img src="///images/images/Eowyn.jpg" style="width: 274px" /></p>
    </div>
       <div>
   
        <h3>Théoden</h3>
        <p>The King of Rohan who regains his strength after being manipulated by Saruman. He leads his riders bravely at Helm’s Deep and Pelennor Fields.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;<img src="~/images/images/King%20of%20Rohan.jpg" style="width: 268px; height: 345px" /></p>
    </div>


       <div>
        <h3>Gollum</h3>
        <p>Once a hobbit-like creature named Sméagol, twisted by centuries of obsession with the Ring. He guides Frodo and Sam, torn constantly between loyalty and greed.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;<img src="///images/Gollum.jpg" style="width: 295px" /></p>
    </div>

       <div>
        <h3>Saruman</h3>
        <p>Originally the head of the wizards, but corrupted by desire for power and knowledge. He betrays his allies and attempts to build his own army.</p>
    <p><img src="///images/Saruman.jpg" style="width: 339px" /></p>
    </div>

    <div>
        <h3>Sauron</h3>
        <p>The Dark Lord who forged the One Ring to control Middle-earth. Though rarely seen in person, his influence spreads fear and corruption everywhere.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;<img src="///images/Sauron.jpg" style="width: 330px" /></p>
    </div>
       <div>
        <h3>Galadriel</h3>
        <p>Lady of Lothlórien, one of the most powerful elves in Middle-earth, She offers guidance, gifts, and protection to the Fellowship.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;<img src="///images/Lady%20Galadriel.jpg" style="width: 311px" /></p>
    </div>

     <div>
        <h3>Elrond</h3>
        <p>Lord of Rivendell and keeper of great wisdom.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;<img src="///images/Elrond.jpg" style="width: 268px; height: 421px" /></p>
    </div>

    <div>
    
        <h3>Bilbo Baggins</h3>
        <p>Frodo’s uncle and the original finder of the Ring. Cheerful and adventurous, he inspires Frodo and begins the story that changes Middle-earth.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;<img src="///images/Bilbo.jpg" style="width: 301px" /></p>
    </div>



